Text.Value: My memories before the nautiloid are shrouded in darkness.
The destruction we wrought at the Last Light. Did it not give you a thrill of pleasure?
Beggars can't be choosers. Such a powerful form should serve us well in the chaos to come.
As regards to your own morbid little fantasies, I'm sure they're nothing to worry about. So long as they remain fantasies.
So long as our quest leads us to the destruction of the Absolute, I suppose we should continue on together. But I tell you now - I've no interest in serving any god, Bhaal or otherwise.
What's done is done, I suppose. But I'd be loathe to cause such destruction again. Not unless the alternative is far, far worse.
I'm sure that will be of small comfort to her.
I can hardly hold you responsible for what you do while unconscious, but still... I'll sleep with one eye open. Better safe than, well, dead.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly nervous, but not wanting to hurt or offend you

Text.Value: Then again, our case isn't exactly usual. Perhaps whatever's causing our tadpoles to remain in stasis has also affected your mind.

EditorData.NodeContext: Curious, trying to see if an answer springs to mind

Text.Value: I know the truth about myself at last. I'm a Bhaalspawn.
Bhaal has given me his decree. I will lead us on to victory as his Chosen.
Total amnesia isn't usually a symptom of ceremorphosis. If it is, they've forgotten to write it down in any text I've read on the subject.

EditorData.NodeContext: Curious, trying to see if an answer springs to mind

Text.Value: If ceremorphosis takes place, all trace of your former self will be subsumed into the mind flayer's hive. So, to still be here, if a mite forgetful? Still a win in my book.
The vile urge within me has been scourged. My heart is pure at last.
I once wished a most impure demise on a colleague of mine who bought the last remaining copy of Etheril's Enchiridion of Enchanting Easements. First edition, too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost tutting/shaking his head. A disappointing memory.

Text.Value: What did you make of my improved form?
A Bhaalspawn? Gosh.
Can't say that it did. I'm not entirely sure we made the right decision there, if I'm being honest with you.
Nothing like ridding oneself of a god's unwanted influence to lighten the load on your shoulders.
The Chosen of Bhaal? I can think of a few gods I'd rather serve, to be honest.
I tried to kill you in my sleep. What if I do it again?
I wasn't sure if we'd lose you to that darkness entirely. I'm glad to know you've found your way back to us.
What's on your mind?
I swear, what happened to Alfira - it wasn't my fault.
As long as it absorbs Weave of its own kind it remains stable - to an extent. The moment it becomes unstable, however...
Honestly, I didn't know you had it in you. A dark destroyer in our midsts.
Actually, there are other topics I wish to discuss.
I have violent thoughts. Depraved thoughts. Ones that refuse to go away...
We all have those from time to time.
Entirely up to you. What's on your mind?
I know what it is to have a closer connection than most with the gods. But with Bhaal... that's not a bond I'd like to be bound with. You should be careful. Very, very careful.

EditorData.NodeContext: Giving hesitant advice - Bhaal sin't a god to be trifled with

Text.Value: It's certainly one of the more unsightly shape-shiftings I've seen, but we can't all be blessed with the elegance of an aasimar transforming in the heavens, can we?

Synopsis: Gale's default dialog that triggers whenever you speak to Gale in the game world. Covers a variety of topics that mostly react to Gale-related events that took place.
